        <common:Name xml:lang="en">Public Integrity Indicators</common:Name>
        <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Les indicateurs d'intégrité publique</common:Name>
        <common:Description xml:lang="en"><p>Following the adoption of the <a href="https://www.oecd.org/gov/ethics/recommendation-public-integrity/">OECD Council Recommendation on Public Integrity</a> in 2017, the Public Governance Committee (PGC), via its Working Party of Senior Public Integrity Officials (SPIO) subsidiary body, developed the <a href="https://oecd-public-integrity-indicators.org/">OECD Public Integrity Indicators</a> (PII) to measure the implementation of the OECD Council Recommendation on Public Integrity. The PII are complementary to the <a href="https://www.oecd.org/fr/corruption/oecd-public-integrity-handbook-ac8ed8e8-en.htm\">OECD Public Integrity Handbook</a> and the <a href="https://www.oecd.org/governance/ethics/public-integrity-maturity-models.htm\">OECD Public Integrity Maturity Models</a>.</p><p>The OECD Public Integrity Indicators (PII) measure the quality and effectiveness of public integrity systems across six areas:</p><ul><li>Quality of Strategic Framework (data available)</li><li>Accountability of Public Policymaking &ndash; covering conflict-of-interest, political finance, lobbying, public information, open government, and public consultation (data available)</li><li>Effectiveness of Internal Control and Risk Management (data available)</li><li>Integrity and Effectiveness of the Justice System (to be launched in 2024)</li><li>Strength of External Oversight and Control (to be launched in 2024)</li><li>Meritocracy of the Public Sector (to be launched in 2025)</li></ul><p>The OECD Public Integrity Indicators provide cross-country comparative data to help policy makers and practitioners strengthen the resilience of public integrity systems towards corruption risks and prevent the mismanagement and waste of public funds. The PIIs measure the strength of standard regulatory safeguards (<em>de jure</em>) and implementation of these safeguards in practice (<em>de facto</em>). The OECD Secretariat collaborates closely with national administrations to obtain primary data collected directly from a wide range of actors across the executive, legislative and judiciary branches.</p><p>Data is collected for all 38 OECD member states (Australia, Austria, Belgium, Canada, Chile, Colombia, Costa Rica, the Czech Republic, Denmark, Estonia, Finland, France, Germany, Greece, Hungary, Iceland, Ireland, Israel, Italy, Japan, Korea (Republic of), Latvia, Lithuania, Luxembourg, Mexico, the Netherlands, New Zealand, Norway, Poland, Portugal, the Slovak Republic, Slovenia, Spain, Sweden, Switzerland, T&uuml;rkiye, the United Kingdom, and the United States), two adherents to the OECD Recommendation on Public Integrity (Argentina and Peru), and one OECD key partner (Brazil).</p><p>Data is presented for each area as a set of indicators (listed under &ldquo;Measure&rdquo;), which can be further broken down into criteria. Indicator values are calculated by counting the number of criteria fulfilled (based on OECD and other international standards) and expressing as a percentage of the total. Criteria values are binary, with a status of fulfilled represented as a 1 and a status of not fulfilled represented as a 0. Some outcome-level indicators consist of numerical rates calculated based on primary data values, either from administrative data sources (public registries) or surveys.</p><p>&ldquo;Data not available&rdquo; indicates that no data exists. &ldquo;Data not provided&rdquo; represents data that was not provided during the data collection process and &ldquo;Data pending&rdquo; represents data that is still being collected and/or assessed. &ldquo;Not tracking&rdquo; is used to indicate when administrations do not collate existing data into a central statistical measure.</p></common:Description>

        <structure:Code id="FCTR_CAP_PR_A">

      </structure:Codelist>
      <structure:Codelist id="CL_CRITERIA" agencyID="OECD.GOV.PSI" version="1.3" isFinal="true">
        <common:Name xml:lang="en">Criteria code list</common:Name>
        <structure:Code id="PII_131_1">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">10</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Strategic objectives are established for mitigating public integrity risks in human resource management, including violations of of public integrity standards.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_131_2">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">20</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Strategic objectives are established for mitigating public integrity risks in public financial management, including reducing fraud and financial mismanagement.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_131_3">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">30</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Strategic objectives are established for mitigating public integrity risks in internal control and risk management.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_131_4">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">40</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Strategic objectives are established for mitigating public integrity risks in public procurement.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_131_5">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">50</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Strategic objectives are established for reducing fraud and other types of corruption across the public sector.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_131_6">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">60</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Strategic objectives are established to mitigate public integrity risks in the private sector, public corporations, state-owned enterprises or public-private partnerships.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_131_7">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">70</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Strategies for any of the following sectors have at least one first-level objective aimed at mitigating public integrity risks: (a) infrastructure, (b) housing, (c) health, (d) education, (e) taxation, (f) customs.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_132_1">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">80</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Within the last five years, an inter-institutional body has prepared and published an analytical report on public integrity risks that formulates recommendations and sets priorities for the whole public integrity system.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_132_2">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">90</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Each existing strategy is based on an assessment of public integrity risks, identifying as a minimum specific types of relevant integrity breaches, the actors likely to be involved, as well as the expected likelihood and impact if the risk materialises.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_132_3">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">100</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Each existing strategy refers to at least 4 out of the following 8 sources of information related to public integrity: (a) indicators from international organisations or research institutions, (b) employee surveys, (c) household surveys, (d) business surveys, (e) other survey data, such as user surveys, or polls from local research institutions, (f) data from public registries (e.g. law enforcement, audit institutions, national statistics office), (g) published research documents from national or international organisations or academia (e.g. articles, reports, working papers, political economy analysis) and (h) commissioned research.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_133_1">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">110</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">All strategies include a situation analysis, including identification of existing public integrity risks.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_133_2">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">120</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">All strategies contain outcome-level indicators for the public integrity objectives.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_133_3">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">130</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">All strategies set target values for all outcome-level indicators.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_133_4">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">140</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">At least one strategy refers to at least one international legal instrument relating to public integrity.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_134_1">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">150</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">A minimum duration of at least 2 weeks for inter-governmental and public consultation period is established in legislation.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_134_2">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">160</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The public consultation portal contains the draft strategy, including all supporting relevant materials.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_134_3">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">170</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">All public integrity strategies in force have undergone mandatory inter-governmental and public consultation processes.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_134_4">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">180</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">At least one public integrity strategy has undergone an extended consultation process.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_134_5">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">190</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">At least one key integrity body has been consulted and provided inputs through the regular intergovernmental or public consultation procedures to at least one of the existing public integrity strategies.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_134_6">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">200</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">At least one non-state actor has been a member of a working group mandated to develop or amend public integrity strategies in force.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_134_7">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">210</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The public consultation portal contains a summary sheet for all draft strategies with responses to all submitted comments provided during the public consultation.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_135_1">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">220</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">For each strategy, there is a central coordination function responsible for coordinating the implementation, monitoring, reporting, and evaluation of the action plan.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_135_2">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">230</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">All public integrity strategies have an action plan in force.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_135_3">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">240</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">All action plans include objectives with dedicated outcome-level indicators, baseline targets, and a list of activities.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_135_4">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">250</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">All action plans identify lead organisations at least for each objective.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_135_5">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">260</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">All action plans contain a section specifying the monitoring, reporting, and evaluation arrangements.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_135_6">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">270</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">All action plans reference administrative data sources from existing public registries.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_135_7">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">280</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">At least one action plan includes data sources from staff, household, or business surveys.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_135_8">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">290</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">At least one action plan includes activities to collaborate with institutions at the subnational level.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_135_9">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">300</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">All action plans are published as a minimum on the website of the responsible body.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_135_10">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">310</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Monitoring reports are published for all action plans, at least once a year, and publicly available no later than 3 months after the defined reporting schedule.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_135_11">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">320</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">All monitoring reports report on progress against pre-defined indicators and targets in the action plan.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_135_12">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">330</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">All monitoring reports present the rate of implementation for activities in the action plan.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_135_13">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">340</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">All monitoring reports draw conclusions and have a dedicated section with recommendations to management.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_135_14">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">350</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The responsible body(ies) have initiated consultations with relevant state administration bodies to discuss the monitoring report(s) during the latest full calendar year.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_135_15">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">360</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">At least one responsible body has initiated consultations with the general public and/or civil society organisations on its monitoring reports during the latest full calendar year or the year prior to that.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_136_1">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">370</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Implementation of activities (%)</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_137_1">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">380</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">All action plans include estimates for capital and operational expenditures.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_137_2">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">390</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Additional costs are identified and a cost estimate is provided for specific activities.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_137_3">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">400</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Financial plans are multi-annual and linked with the medium-term expenditure framework.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_137_4">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">410</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">No funding shortfalls or budget reductions against the approved action plan have been reported by the implementing authorities or in the monitoring reports.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_138_1">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">420</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">An evaluation report exists for all predecessor strategies.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_138_2">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">430</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">All evaluation reports for predecessor strategies have been published online by the national authorities.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_138_3">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">440</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Non-state actors were involved in the evaluation of at least one of the predecessor strategies, either as evaluators or as part of a formal review/quality assurance mechanism.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_138_4">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">450</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Current strategies all have an end-of-term evaluation listed as an activity in their action plan.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_138_5">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">460</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Current strategies have all used evidence from evaluations of predecessor strategies to inform their approach.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3101_1">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">470</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The definition of IC and IA in policy or regulatory documents are defined according to international standards.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3101_2">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">480</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Regulations on IC define managerial responsibility regarding the implementation of IC and IA.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3101_3">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">490</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Regulations specify the objectives of IC.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3101_4">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">500</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Regulations on IC establish annual IC and IA reporting activities.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3101_5">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">510</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Guidelines on fraud and corruption prevention are available and part of the IC system.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3101_6">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">520</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Regulations for implementing internal control are applicable to all central government institutions, including social security funds.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3101_7">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">530</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Standards of conduct and ethical behaviour are published and applicable for ministers.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3101_8">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">540</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Standards of conduct and ethical behaviour are published and applicable for members of parliament.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3101_9">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">550</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Standards of conduct and ethical behaviour are published and applicable for other political appointees.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3101_10">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">560</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Standards of conduct and ethical behaviour are published and applicable for civil servants.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3102_1">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">570</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The regulatory framework specifies the operational arrangements for IA.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3102_2">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">580</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The regulatory framework specifies the scope of work and size of IA units (minimum two persons per unit).</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3102_3">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">590</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The regulatory framework allows IA arrangements to differ depending on the type and size of the institution.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3102_4">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">600</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Standards directly aimed at the conduct and ethical behaviour of internal auditors are published.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3102_5">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">610</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The regulatory framework stipulates that the head of the IA function has direct and unrestricted access to political staff and senior managers of all public sector bodies.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3102_6">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">620</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The regulatory framework stipulates the independence of the IA function in determining the scope of internal auditing, performing work, and communicating results.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3102_7">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">630</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The regulatory framework prohibits or establishes cooling-off periods for internal audit staff to audit operations for which they have previously been responsible to avoid any perceived conflict of interest.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3102_8">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">640</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The regulatory framework requires the Internal Audit Units (IAUs) to develop an internal audit activity manual based on a standard methodology approved by the CHU or a central IA function</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3102_9">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">650</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The regulatory framework requires external quality assessments of IA activity to be performed no less than once in 5 years by an independent party.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3102_10">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">660</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The regulatory framework stipulates that the head of IAU must provide annual activity reports to the CHU or the central IA function.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3103_1">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">670</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">A risk management framework exists.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3103_2">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">680</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Public integrity risks are explicitly addressed in the risk management framework.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3103_3">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">690</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The risk management framework explicitly delegates responsibility for conducting risk assessments to management, not internal auditors.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3103_4">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">700</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Entity-wide risk registers or fraud risk profiles must be prepared in each public body.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3103_5">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">710</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Processes and procedures are established for addressing the risks and actions that management must take, including reporting procedures or addressing weaknesses in the internal control system.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3104_1">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">720</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">One central government body (CHU) develops the IC and IA systems.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3104_2">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">730</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">A central function develops the IC system.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3104_3">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">740</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">A central function develops the IA system.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3104_4">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">750</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The CHU promotes IC and IA methodologies based on international standards.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3104_5">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">760</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">A central function promotes IC methodologies based on international standards.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3104_6">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">770</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">A central function promotes IA methodologies based on international standards.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3104_7">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">780</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The CHU has conducted a government-wide review on the IC and IA systems, annually during the last 3 years.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3104_8">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">790</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The central function has conducted a government-wide review of the IC system, annually during the last 3 years.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3104_9">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">800</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The central function has conducted a government-wide review of the IA system, annually during the last 3 years.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3104_10">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">810</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The CHU or the central IA function coordinates the training and certification system to ensure the inclusion of new IA staff and continuous professional education.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3104_11">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">820</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Guidelines on assessing integrity risks have been issued within the last 5 years by the CHU or the central function for IC to all public sector institutions implementing IC.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3105_1">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">830</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">All central government institutions that are required to implement IC reported on actions taken to the central function responsible for IC policy in the latest full calendar year.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3105_2">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">840</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The annual reports on IC or IA from the past 3 years present the rates of implementation of IA recommendations.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3105_3">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">850</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The annual reports on IC and IA for the past 3 years are publicly available.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3105_4">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">860</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The annual reports on IC and IA were shared with the SAI for the past three years, if not publicly available.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3105_5">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">870</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The latest annual reports on IC from the past 3 years included summary statistics of auditing, and a summary of selfassessments of internal control and risk management activities.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3105_6">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">880</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The latest annual report on IC or IA contained a dedicated section or data on integrity, anti-corruption or fraud risks and controls.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3105_7">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">890</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">More than 50% of public bodies covered by IC provided a self-assessment report regarding the maturity of their IC systems during the latest full calendar year.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3105_8">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">900</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">An intergovernmental organisation has conducted a review of the IC or IA system within the past 5 years.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3105_9">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">910</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The SAI has conducted a review of the IC or IA system within the past 5 years.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3106_1">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">920</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">IA units are staffed according to legal requirements.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3106_2">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">930</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">IA units are staffed by at least 2 auditors.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3106_3">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">940</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">A certification scheme for IA professionals is operational at the national level.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3106_4">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">950</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">At least 85% of public officials performing internal audit functions have obtained a national or international certificate for IA.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3106_5">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">960</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Audit charters are adopted by heads of institutions for all sample organisations.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3106_6">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">970</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Audit procedure manuals are adopted by heads of institutions for all sample organisations.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3106_7">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">980</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Reports from the IA unit are submitted directly to the head of the institution for all sample organisations.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3106_8">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">990</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Annual activity reports from all the IA units are submitted to the CHU or the central IA function.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3106_9">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1000</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Audit plans in all sample organisations use data from an entity-wide risk register and the IA function’s risk assessment to select areas to audit within the defined audit universe.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3106_10">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1010</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Audit plans in at least half of sample organisations include integrity-specific objectives aimed at reducing fraud and other public integrity risks.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3106_11">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1020</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">At least 90% of IA reports include the results of IC assessment in the audited area.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3106_12">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1030</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">At least half of sample organisations conducted external quality assurance of the IA function within the last 5 years.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3107_1">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1040</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">All sample organisations have conducted at least one risk assessment exercise in the past 3 years.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3107_2">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1050</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Roles and responsibilities for risk management and for managing integrity risks have been assigned in all budget organisations, in line with the regulatory framework.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3107_3">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1060</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">All sample organisations have established a system for documenting the results of risk assessments, including as a minimum creating risk profiles or risk registers.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3107_4">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1070</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The IA function has reviewed the adequacy and effectiveness of the risk management policies and processes for all public sector bodies within the past 3 years.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3107_5">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1080</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The body with direct responsibility for managing integrity risks is not part of the IA function and reports directly to the head of the institution in all sample organisations.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3107_6">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1090</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The body with direct responsibility for managing integrity risks is not part of the compliance department or legal counsel in all sample organisations.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3107_7">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1100</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Guidance documents on managing integrity risks, including red flags for corruption and fraud risks that are relevant for the entity’s operations, exist for at least half of sample organisations.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3107_8">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1110</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Risk assessments for at least half of sample organisations identify integrity risks.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3107_9">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1120</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Integrity risk assessments for at least half of sample organisations identify both inherent and residual risks.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3107_10">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1130</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Integrity risk assessments for at least half of sample organisations include an examination of existing controls and whether changes are needed in the control environment (i.e. risk treatment).</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3107_11">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1140</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Integrity risk assessments for at least half of sample organisations apply either a qualitative or quantitative scoring methodology (e.g. risk likelihood, impact and velocity) that enables prioritisation of high versus low risks.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3108_1">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1150</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Number of first-level budget organisation</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3109_1">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1160</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Adoption rate for internal audit recommendations</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_31010_1">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1170</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Implementation rate for internal audit recommendations</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_31011_1">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1180</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Implementation rate for internal audit recommendations.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3131_1">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1190</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The regulatory framework provides that all public institutions and private persons carrying out public duties are holders of public information; and that everyone, including non-citizens and legal persons, has the right to access information in all the forms available.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3131_2">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1200</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The only restrictions to access to public information allowed are listed by law and are in line with the Tromso Convention.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3131_3">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1210</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">There are statutory deadlines for processing requests for information.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3131_4">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1220</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Information holders are required to provide information in the requested format; requesters are not required to provide justification for their requests.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3131_5">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1230</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The right to appeal to an independent body or the court against refusal or inactivity of an administrative body is ensured.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3131_6">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1240</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Information requested is always provided free of charge.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3131_7">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1250</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">A list of datasets and mandatory information to be disclosed is defined in the regulatory framework.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3131_8">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1260</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Primary legislation specifies that Government data are “open by default” (except for specific cases defined in the regulatory framework).</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3131_9">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1270</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Decisions of the public body specialised in public information cannot be quashed by any executive body.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3132_1">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1280</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Lobbying activities are defined in the regulatory framework, including which actors are considered as lobbyists.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3132_2">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1290</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Cooling off periods for public officials are established in the regulatory framework.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3132_3">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1300</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Cooling off periods for lobbyists are established in the regulatory framework.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3132_4">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1310</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Regulations list incompatibilities between public functions and other public or private activities.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3132_5">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1320</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Regulations define circumstances and relationships that can lead to conflict-of-interest situations for public officials and establish the obligation to manage them.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3132_6">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1330</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Regulations define institutional responsibilities as well as submission, compliance, and content verification procedures for conflict-of-interest or interest declarations.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3132_7">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1340</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Any member of the Government must submit an interest declaration, as a minimum upon entry and any renewal or change in public office.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3132_8">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1350</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Any member of the parliament must submit an interest declaration, as a minimum upon entry and any renewal or change in public office.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3132_9">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1360</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Any member of the highest bodies of the judiciary must submit an interest declaration, as a minimum upon entry and any renewal or change in public office.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3132_10">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1370</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Any public employee in a high-risk position must submit an interest declaration, as a minimum upon entry and any renewal or change in public office.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3132_11">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1380</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Any newly appointed or reappointed top-tier civil servant of the executive branch must submit an interest declaration.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3132_12">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1390</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Sanctions for breaches of conflict-of-interest provisions are defined and proportional to the severity of the offence.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3132_13">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1400</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Sanctions for breaches of political finance and election campaign regulations are defined and proportional to the severity of the offence.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3132_14">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1410</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Sanctions for breaches of standards for transparency and integrity in lobbying are defined and proportional to the severity of the offence.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3132_15">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1420</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
