          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Electoral candidates can be held personally liable for breaches and be sanctioned.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3132_16">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1430</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Regulations ban anonymous donations, and all contributions made to political parties and/or candidates must be registered and reported.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3132_17">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1440</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Regulations ban contributions from foreign states or enterprises.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3132_18">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1450</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Regulations ban contributions from publicly owned enterprises.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3132_19">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1460</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Electoral campaign expenses for parties, candidates and third parties are limited to a ceiling.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3132_20">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1470</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Parties and/or candidates must report their finances (funding and expenses) during electoral campaigns.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3132_21">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1480</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Regulations ban the use of public funds and resources in favour of or against a political party.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3132_22">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1490</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Regulations set a threshold for personal contributions to candidates’ personal campaigns.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3132_23">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1500</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Political parties must make financial reports public, including all contributions exceeding a fixed ceiling.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3132_24">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1510</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Beneficial ownership rules make mandatory the disclosure of company data to identify owners of corporations, establish a central register, and make information accessible to the public.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3133_1">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1520</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">A supervisory body responsible for public information issues is established.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3133_2">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1530</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The management board or the head of the supervisory body for public information is appointed for a fixed term and can be dismissed during this term only in strictly defined cases.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3133_3">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1540</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Appeals against decisions of the body specialised in public information are decided by a body independent of all parties.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3133_4">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1550</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Statistical data on requests for access to information and decisions have been aggregated and published by a relevant public body for the past three years.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3133_5">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1560</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Inspections of compliance were conducted by the relevant supervisory body within the latest full calendar year.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3133_6">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1570</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Sanctions for non-compliance were imposed by the relevant supervisory body within the latest full calendar year.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3133_7">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1580</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">A central government unit or independent body is responsible for open data policy.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3133_8">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1590</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">A monitoring function for open data policy is established at the level of the central government.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3134_1">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1600</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">All agendas of formal government sessions have been made publicly available online prior to the session within the latest full calendar year.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3134_2">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1610</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Records of all decisions agreed upon at the government sessions (minutes) are kept.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3134_3">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1620</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Ministers’ agenda are made publicly available online, on their respective ministry website or aggregated on one government website, and specify who was met by the minister, in which capacity, and the topic that was discussed during the meeting.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3135_1">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1630</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The submission rate of interest declarations from members of the Government is 100% for the past six years.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3135_2">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1640</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The submission rate of interest declarations from members of parliament is at least 90% for the past six years.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3135_3">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1650</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The submission rate of interest declarations from members of the highest bodies of the judiciary is at least 80% for the past four years.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3135_4">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1660</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">The submission rate of mandatory interest declarations from newly appointed or reappointed top-tier civil servants of the executive branch is at least 80% for the past four years.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3135_5">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1670</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Declarations to be verified are selected according a risk-based approach.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3135_6">
          <common:Annotations>
            <common:Annotation id="@SDMX">
              <common:AnnotationType>ORDER</common:AnnotationType>
              <common:AnnotationText xml:lang="en">1680</common:AnnotationText>
            </common:Annotation>
          </common:Annotations>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">At least 60% of declarations filed during the latest two full calendar years were verified by the responsible authority.</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="PII_3135_7">

      <structure:Codelist id="CL_CONF_STATUS" agencyID="SDMX" version="1.2" isFinal="true">
        <common:Name xml:lang="en">Confidentiality Status</common:Name>
        <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Statut de confidentialité</common:Name>
        <structure:Code id="F">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Free (free for publication)</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Libre (libre pour publication)</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Used for observations without any special sensitivity considerations and which can thus be freely shared. Usually, source organisations provide information and guidance on general requirements for re-dissemination  (like mentioning the source) either on their websites or in their paper publications. In some institutional environments the term "unclassified" is used in a sense that still denotes implied restrictions in the circulation of information. If this is the case, the organisations concerned may probably consider that "free" (value F) is not the appropriate tag for this kind of "unclassified" category and that "Not for publication, restricted for internal use only" (value N) may be more appropriate.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="N">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Not for publication, restricted for internal use only</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Non destiné à la publication, réservé à un usage interne uniquement</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Used to denote observations that are restricted for internal use only within organisations. This code may be accompanied with an additional observation-level attribute: CONF_REDIST which defines the secondary recipient(s) to whom the sender allows the primary recipient to forward confidential data.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="C">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Confidential statistical information</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Information statistique confidentielle</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Confidential statistical information (primary confidentiality) due to identifiable respondents. Measures also should be taken to prevent not only direct access, but also indirect deduction or calculation by other users and parties, probably by considering and treating additional observations as "confidential" (secondary confidentiality management).</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="D">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Secondary confidentiality set by the sender, not for publication</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Confidentialité secondaire définie par l'expéditeur, non destinée à la publication</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Used by the sender of the data to flag (beyond the confidential statistical information) additional observations in the dataset so that the receiver knows that he/she should suppress these observations in subsequent stages of processing (especially dissemination) in order to prevent third parties to indirectly deduct the observations that are genuinely flagged with "C".</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="S">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Secondary confidentiality set and managed by the receiver, not for publication</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Confidentialité secondaire définie et gérée par le destinataire, pas pour publication</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">If senders do not manage the secondary confidentiality in their data and/or there are also other countries' data involved (with the intention to eventually compile a regional-wide aggregate that is going to be published), the value "S" is used by the receiver to flag additional suppressed observations (within sender's data and/or within the datasets of other senders) in subsequent stages of processing (especially, dissemination) in order to prevent third parties to indirectly deduct the observations that were genuinely flagged with "C" by the sender.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="A">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Primary confidentiality due to small counts</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Confidentialité primaire en raison des petits comptes</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">A cell is flagged as confidential if less than m units ("too few units") contribute to the total of that cell. The limits of what constitutes "small counts" can vary across statistical domains, countries, etc.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="O">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Primary confidentiality due to dominance by one unit</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Confidentialité primaire due à la dominance d'une unité</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Used when one unit accounts for more than x % of the total of a cell. The value of x can vary across statistical domains or countries, be influenced by legislation, etc.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="T">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Primary confidentiality due to dominance by two units</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Confidentialité primaire due à la dominance de deux unités</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Used when two units account for more than x % of the total of a cell. The value of x can vary across statistical domains or countries, be influenced by legislation, etc.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="G">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Primary confidentiality due to dominance by one or two units</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Confidentialité primaire due à la dominance d'une ou deux unités</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Used when one or two units account(s) for more than x % of the total of a cell. The value of x can vary across statistical domains or countries, be influenced by legislation, etc.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="M">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Primary confidentiality due to data declared confidential based on other measures of concentration</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Confidentialité primaire due aux données déclarées confidentielles sur la base d'autres mesures de concentration</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Cells declared confidential using mathematical definitions of sensitive cells, e.g. p-percent, p/q or (n,k) rules.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="E">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Not for publication, restricted for internal use only (equivalent to the code N) until the embargo time elapses; Free for publication (equivalent to the code F) after the embargo time elapses.</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Non destiné à la publication, réservé à un usage interne uniquement (équivalent au code N) jusqu'à l'expiration du délai d'embargo ; Libre de publication (équivalent au code F) après l'expiration du délai d'embargo.</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Used for embargoed data. The embargo time has to be specified in the EMBARGO_TIME attribute. This code may be accompanied with an additional observation-level attribute: CONF_REDIST which defines the secondary recipient(s) to whom the sender allows the primary recipient to forward confidential data.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
      </structure:Codelist>
      <structure:Codelist id="CL_DECIMALS" agencyID="SDMX" version="1.0" isFinal="true">
        <common:Name xml:lang="en">Decimals</common:Name>
        <common:Description xml:lang="en">This code list provides a list of values showing the number of decimal digits used in the data. This code list was released in 2009. More information about this code list and SDMX code lists in general (e.g. list of generic codes for expressing general concepts like "Total", "Unknown", etc.; syntaxes for the creation of further codes; general guidelines for the creation of SDMX code lists) can be found at this address: https://sdmx.org/?page_id=4345.</common:Description>
        <structure:Code id="0">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Zero</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="1">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">One</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="2">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Two</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="3">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Three</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="4">

        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="5">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Five</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="6">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Six</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="7">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Seven</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="8">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Eight</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="9">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Nine</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="10">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Ten</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="11">

        <structure:Code id="14">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Fourteen</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="15">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Fifteen</common:Name>
        </structure:Code>
      </structure:Codelist>
      <structure:Codelist id="CL_FREQ" agencyID="SDMX" version="2.1" isFinal="true">
        <common:Name xml:lang="en">Code list for concept "Frequency"</common:Name>
        <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Codelist pour le concept "Fréquence"</common:Name>
        <common:Description xml:lang="en">This code list provides a set of values indicating
					the "frequency" of the data (e.g. weekly, monthly, quarterly). The concept
					"frequency" may refer to various stages in the production process, e.g. data
					collection or data dissemination. For example, a time series could be
					disseminated at annual frequency but the underlying data are compiled monthly.
					The code list is applicable for all different uses of
					"frequency".</common:Description>
        <common:Description xml:lang="fr">Cette liste de codes fournit un ensemble de valeurs
					indiquant la "fréquence" des données (par exemple, hebdomadaire, mensuelle,
					trimestrielle). Le concept de "fréquence" peut faire référence à différentes
					étapes du processus de production, par ex. collecte ou diffusion de données. Par
					exemple, une série chronologique pourrait être diffusée à une fréquence
					annuelle, mais les données sous-jacentes sont compilées mensuellement. La liste
					de codes est applicable pour toutes les différentes utilisations de
					"fréquence".</common:Description>
        <structure:Code id="A">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Annual</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Annuelle</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used for data collected or disseminated
						every year</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="A2">
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Biennale</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Biennial</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used for data collected or disseminated
						every two years</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="A3">
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Triennale</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Triennial</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used for data collected or disseminated
						every three years</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="A4">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Quadrennial</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Quadriennale</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used for data collected or disseminated
						every four years</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="A5">
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Quinquennale</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Quinquennial</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used for data collected or disseminated
						every five years</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="A10">
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Décennale</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Decennial</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used for data collected or disseminated
						every ten years</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="A20">
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Bidécennal</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Bidecennial</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used for data collected or disseminated
						every twenty years</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="A30">
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Tridécennal</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Tridecennial</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used for data collected or disseminated
						every thirty years</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="A_3">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Three times a year</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Trois fois par an</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used for data collected or disseminated
						three times a year</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="S">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Half-yearly, semester</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Semestrielle</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used for data collected or disseminated
						every semester</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="Q">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Quarterly</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Trimestrielle</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used for data collected or disseminated
						every quarter</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="M">
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Mensuelle</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Monthly</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used for data collected or disseminated
						every month</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="M2">
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Bimestrielle</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Bimonthly</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used for data collected or disseminated
						every two months</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="M_2">
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Semi-mensuelle</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Semimonthly</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used for data collected or disseminated
						twice a month</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="M_3">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Three times a month</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Trois fois par mois</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used for data collected or disseminated
						three times a month</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="W">
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Hebdomadaire</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Weekly</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used for data collected or disseminated
						every week</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="W2">
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Aux 2 semaines</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Biweekly</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used for data collected or disseminated
						every two weeks</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="W3">
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Aux 3 semaines</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Triweekly</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used for data collected or disseminated
						every three weeks</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="W4">
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Aux 4 semaines</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Four-weekly</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used for data collected or disseminated
						every four weeks</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="W_2">
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Bihebdomadaire</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Semiweekly</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used for data collected or disseminated
						twice a week</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="W_3">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Three times a week</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Trois fois par semaine</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used for data collected or disseminated
						three times a week</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="D">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Daily</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Quotidienne</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used for data collected or disseminated
						every day</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="D_2">
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Deux fois par jour</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Twice a day</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used for data collected or disseminated
						twice a day</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="H">
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Horaire</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Hourly</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used for data collected or disseminated
						every hour</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="H2">
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Bihoraire</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Bihourly</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used for data collected or disseminated
						every two hours</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="H3">
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Trihoraire</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Trihourly</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used for data collected or disseminated
						every three hours</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="B">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Daily – business week</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Jours ouvrable</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Similar to "daily", however there are no
						observations for Saturdays and Sundays (so, neither “missing values” nor
						“numeric values” should be provided for Saturday and
						Sunday)</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="N">
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Chaque minute</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Minutely</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">While N denotes "minutely", usually, there may be
						no observations every minute (for several series the frequency is usually
						"irregular" within a day/days). And though observations may be sparse (not
						collected or disseminated every minute), missing values do not need to be
						given for the minutes when no observations exist: in any case the time stamp
						determines when an observation is observed</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="I">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Irregular</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Irrégulière</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used with irregular time series that stores
						data for a sequence of arbitrary timepoints. Irregular time series are
						appropriate when the data arrives unpredictably, such as when the
						application records every stock trade or when random events are recorded
						(the interval between each element can be a different
						length)</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="OA">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Occasional annual</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Occasionnelle annuelle</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">The event occurs occasionally with an infrequent
						update that could span from 1 year to several years between events. It
						implies a survey that experiences a gap for several years prior to the next
						survey update (this is commonly linked to funding available to run a
						specific survey (i.e. health surveys), whereas a regular annual survey
						refers typically to ‘programs’ that are funded regularly and fall under the
						Statistics Act, and therefore never experience a gap)</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="OM">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Occasional monthly</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Occasionnelle mensuelle</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">The event occurs occasionally with an infrequent
						update that could span from 1 month to several months between events. It
						implies a survey that experiences a gap for several months prior to the next
						survey update</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="_O">
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Autre</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Other</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used when the qualitative or quantitative
						values that a variable takes in a data set is associated to multiple
						occurrences with frequency other than the already defined ones (for example
						every 5 hours and 32 minutes etc.)</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="_U">
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">Non spécifié</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Unspecified</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used when a set of values are reported
						within a time range but not associated to sub ranges. Often this could
						happen in case of missing or sparse information. (Let’s say we have two
						observations for 2020 but we do not know if they are part of a monthly
						reporting or quarterly reporting)</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="_Z">
          <common:Name xml:lang="fr">N'est pas applicable</common:Name>
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Not applicable</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used when the qualitative or quantitative
						values that a variable takes in a data set is not associated to multiple
						occurrences (only single occurrence exists) one can use the _Z as
						frequency</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
      </structure:Codelist>
      <structure:Codelist id="CL_OBS_STATUS" agencyID="SDMX" version="2.2" isFinal="true">
        <common:Name xml:lang="en">Observation Status</common:Name>
        <structure:Code id="A">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Normal value</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">To be used as default value if no value is provided or when no special coded qualification is assumed. Usually, it can be assumed that the source agency assigns sufficient confidence to the provided observation and/or the value is not expected to be dramatically revised.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="B">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Time series break</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Observations are characterised as such when different content exists or a different methodology has been applied to this observation as compared with the preceding one (the one given for the previous period).</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="D">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Definition differs</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Used to indicate slight deviations from the established methodology (footnote-type information); these divergences do not imply a break in time series.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="E">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Estimated value</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Observation obtained through an estimation methodology (e.g. to produce back-casts) or based on the use of a limited amount of data or ad hoc sampling and through additional calculations (e.g. to produce a value at an early stage of the production stage while not all data are available). It may also be used in case of experimental data (e.g. in the context of a pilot ahead of a full scale production process) or in case of data of (anticipated/assessed) low quality. If needed, additional information can be provided through free text using the COMMENT_OBS attribute at the observation level or at a higher level. This code is to be used when the estimation is done by a sender agency. When the imputation is carried out by a receiver agency in order to replace or fill gaps in reported data series, the flag to use is I "Value imputed by a receiving agency".</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="F">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Forecast value</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Value deemed to assess the magnitude which a quantity will assume at some future point of time (as distinct from "estimated value" which attempts to assess the magnitude of an already existent quantity).</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="G">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Experimental value</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Data collected on the basis of definitions or (alternative) collection methods under development. Data not of guaranteed quality as normally expected from provider.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="I">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Value imputed by a receiving agency</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Observation imputed by a receiving agency to replace or fill gaps in reported data series. This code is intended to cover all cases where a receiving agency publishes data about a sending agency that do not come from an official source in the sender agency's reporting framework. When the estimation is done by the sender agency, the flag to use is E "Estimated value".</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="K">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Data included in another category</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">This code is used when data for a given category are missing and are included in another category, sub-total or total. Generally where code "K" is used there should be a corresponding code "W - Includes data from another category" assigned to the over-covered category. Implementers and data reporters should use the COMMENT_OBS observation-level attribute to specify under which category the data are included.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="W">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Includes data from another category</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">This code is used when data include another category, or go beyond the scope of the data collection and are therefore over-covered. Generally, where code "W" is used there should be a corresponding code "K - Data included in another category" assigned to the category which is under-covered. Implementers and data reporters should use the COMMENT_OBS observation-level attribute to specify which additional data are included.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="O">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Missing value</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">This code is to be used when no breakdown is made between the reasons why data are missing. Data can be missing due to many reasons: data cannot exist, data exist but are not collected (e.g. because they are below a certain threshold or subject to a derogation clause), data are unreliable, etc.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="M">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Missing value; data cannot exist</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Used to denote empty cells resulting from the impossibility to collect a statistical value (e.g. a particular education level or type of institution may be not applicable to a given country's education system).</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="P">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Provisional value</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">An observation is characterised as "provisional" when the source agency - while it bases its calculations on its standard production methodology - considers that the data, almost certainly, are expected to be revised.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="S">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Strike and other special events</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Special circumstances (e.g. strike) affecting the observation or causing a missing value.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="L">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Missing value; data exist but were not collected</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Used, for example, when some data are not reported/disseminated because they are below a certain threshold.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="H">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Missing value; holiday or weekend</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Used in some daily data flows.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="Q">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Missing value; suppressed</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Used, for example, when data are suppressed due to statistical confidentiality considerations.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="J">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Derogation</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Clause in an agreement (e.g. legal act, gentlemen's agreement) stating that some provisions in the agreement are not to be implemented by designated parties; these derogations may affect the observation or cause a missing value. In general, derogations are limited in time.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="N">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Not significant</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Used to indicate a value which is not a "real" zero (e.g. a result of 0.0004 rounded to zero).</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="U">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Low reliability</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">This indicates existing observations, but for which the user should also be aware of the low quality assigned.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
        <structure:Code id="V">
          <common:Name xml:lang="en">Unvalidated value</common:Name>
          <common:Description xml:lang="en">Observation as received from the respondent without further evaluation of data quality.</common:Description>
        </structure:Code>
      </structure:Codelist>
